    "The bottle by the door, the scribblings on the notepad express cognitive agency because they are part of a knot in the information processing landscape with a certain kind of structure.",
    "Turned to cognitive purposes by rational agents, these resources are parts of thought not because of any intrinsic property cognitive property they have, but in virtue of their relations to persons -loci of rational agency -and their place in the shared world created by these agents.",
    "Here, we might worry that our explanation has become circular, appealing to a pregiven notion of intentional or rational structure in events to help provide an account of what intentional actions are.",
    "As such, we might worry about how well the Ans-Synthese (2025) 205:47 combean view can be fit into the naturalistic cognitive scientific framework in which HEC is usually situated.",
